.TH "lpfc_poll_store" 9 "lpfc_poll_store" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
lpfc_poll_store \- Set the value of cfg_poll for the adapter
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "ssize_t" lpfc_poll_store
.BI "(struct device *dev "  ","
.BI "struct device_attribute *attr "  ","
.BI "const char *buf "  ","
.BI "size_t count "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
class device that is converted into a Scsi_host.
.IP "attr" 12
device attribute, not used.
.IP "buf" 12
one or more lpfc_polling_flags values.
.IP "count" 12
not used.
.SH "NOTES"
buf contents converted to integer and checked for a valid value.
.SH "RETURN"
-EINVAL if the buffer connot be converted or is out of range
length of the buf on success
